c_0_0.\n- Root cause indicator on pc_0_0:\n  - iptables -S shows a DROP in OUTPUT chain:\n    - -A OUTPUT -m length --length 10:65535 -j DROP\n  - This rule drops virtually all locally generated IP packets (and responses such as ICMP echo-replies), explaining total IP outage while L2/ARP still works.\n- Routing control-plane state (selected):\n  - leaf_router_0_0 has 10.0.0.1/24 on eth8 and BGP-learned routes to all other /24s via spines.\n  - BGP summaries on leaves, spines, and super-spine show all neighbor sessions Established with appropriate prefixes exchanged.\n  - No indications of routing blackholes or missing routes relevant to pc_0_0/pc_0_1 subnets.\n\nConclusions\n- Anomaly present: Yes — complete IP connectivity failure isolated to host pc_0_0.\n- Faulty device: pc_0_0 (end host).\n- Root cause: Host firewall misconfiguration on pc_0_0 (iptables OUTPUT rule dropping packets of length 10–65535), which blocks all outbound IP traffic (including ICMP and responses to inbound probes). The underlay fabric and EBGP control-plane are healthy.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 31628, "output_tokens": 2734, "total_tokens": 34362, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 31232}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1792}}}
